{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-note-template-tsx","path":"/ecto/schemas","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h4 id=\"schemas\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#schemas\" aria-label=\"schemas permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Schemas</h4>\n<p>map data from any source to elixir code</p>\n<h4 id=\"advantage-of-using-schemas-in-queries\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#advantage-of-using-schemas-in-queries\" aria-label=\"advantage of using schemas in queries permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Advantage of using schemas in queries</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>automatic type conversion</li>\n<li>no need for <code class=\"language-text\">select:</code> option</li>\n<li>return value is a struct</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"elixir\"><pre class=\"language-elixir\"><code class=\"language-elixir\"><span class=\"token keyword\">defmodule</span> User <span class=\"token keyword\">do</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">use</span> Ecto<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Schema\n\n  schema <span class=\"token string\">\"users\"</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">do</span>\n    field<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token atom symbol\">:firstname</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token atom symbol\">:string</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    field<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token atom symbol\">:lastname</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token atom symbol\">:string</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n    has_many<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token atom symbol\">:posts</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> Post<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n    timestamps<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">end</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">end</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">defmodule</span> Post <span class=\"token keyword\">do</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">use</span> Ecto<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Schema\n\n  schema <span class=\"token string\">\"posts\"</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">do</span>\n    field<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token atom symbol\">:title</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token atom symbol\">:string</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    field<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token atom symbol\">:body</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token atom symbol\">:string</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n    belongs_to<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token atom symbol\">:user</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> User<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n    timestamps<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">end</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">end</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># ecto will look for user_id column in posts table</span></code></pre></div>\n<h4 id=\"nested-associations\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#nested-associations\" aria-label=\"nested associations permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Nested Associations</h4>\n<p>you can use <code class=\"language-text\">through</code></p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">belongs_to</code> doesn't work in nested associations</p>\n<h4 id=\"many-to-many-associations\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#many-to-many-associations\" aria-label=\"many to many associations permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Many to many associations</h4>\n<p>needs an extra table / join table</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">join_through</code> option tells ecto where to find the join table</p>\n<h4 id=\"loading-associations\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#loading-associations\" aria-label=\"loading associations permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Loading Associations</h4>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"elixir\"><pre class=\"language-elixir\"><code class=\"language-elixir\">query <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> from<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>user <span class=\"token operator\">in</span> User<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">preload:</span> <span class=\"token atom symbol\">:posts</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\nRepo<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>all<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>query<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># when resource is already loaded, you can use `Repo.preload`</span>\nusers <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> Repo<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>all<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>User<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\nRepo<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>preload<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>users<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token atom symbol\">:posts</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"date":"March 12, 2021","path":"/ecto/schemas","title":"Schemas","category":"Ecto"}}},"pageContext":{}}}